@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{U}                                                                                @{UU}@{APEN 2}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{APEN 2}@{B}P R E F E R E N C E S@{UB}@{APEN 1}
@{U}                                                                                @{UU}@{APEN 2}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{APEN 1}@{JLEFT}
@{BODY}Stratego has several configurable aspects: the screen depth and placement, the
rules, and the sounds are but a few of the many things that you can adjust to
suit you needs or system specifications. The preferences are explained in the
various sections below.
@{PAR}
@{PAR}Stratego comes complete with sounds for all events, but should you wish to
change them you need to copy them into the @{B}Stratego:Samples@{UB} directory
with one of the following names:
@{PAR}
@{CODE}
· @{B}Intro.iff@{UB} - played when Stratego starts up
· @{B}NewGame.iff@{UB} - for when new game is selected
· @{B}EndTurn.iff@{UB} - tells the other player to go
· @{B}Button.iff@{UB} - for button clicks
· @{B}Rescue.iff@{UB} - when a piece is rescued
· @{B}GameWon.iff@{UB} - played when game is won
· @{B}MoveHorse.iff@{UB} - plays when the Scout moves
· @{B}MoveFoot.iff@{UB} - for piece moved (ex: Scout)
· @{B}RemoveBomb.iff@{UB} - when Bomber defuses a bomb
· @{B}Explosion.iff@{UB} - when a piece steps on a bomb
· @{B}Fight1.iff@{UB} - 1 of 2 random fighting sounds
· @{B}Fight2.iff@{UB} - 1 of 2 random fighting so
· @{B}KilledMarshall.iff@{UB} - plays when Marshall dies
· @{B}SpyKilledMarshall.iff@{UB} - when Spy kills Marshall
· @{B}SpyKilled.iff@{UB} - plays when Spy is killed
· @{B}MarshallDefense1.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random for defending
· @{B}MarshallDefense2.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random for defending
· @{B}MarshallDefense3.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random for defending
· @{B}MarshallAttack1.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random for attacking
· @{B}MarshallAttack2.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random for attacking
· @{B}MarshallAttack3.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random for attacking
· @{B}War1.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random sounds during game play
· @{B}War2.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random sounds during game play
· @{B}War3.iff@{UB} - 1 of 3 random sounds during game

@{BODY}@{B}NOTE:@{UB} Make sure the names are spelled correctly, or obviously Stratego will not
find the sound(s) and simply ignore that/those sound(s) and play nothing for the
respective event(s). Similarly, if you do not want to hear a particular sound
you may delete it from the @{B}Stratego:Samples@{UB} directory (or all of them if
you do not wish to hear any sounds).
@{PAR}
@{PAR}@{B}ALSO NOTE@{UB}: The @{B}Intro.iff@{UB} sound sample will only play once Stratego is done
remapping all of the graphics and game play is ready to commence (the mouse
pointer will remain busy during remapping as well).
@{PAR}
@{PAR}@{U}                                                                                @{UU}@{APEN 2}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{PAR}@{CODE}@{JCENTER}@{APEN 2}Preferences Editor@{APEN 1}
@{U}                                                                                @{UU}@{APEN 2}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{APEN 1}@{JLEFT}
@{BODY}The Stratego Preferences Editor was programmed by @{"Chris Page" LINK "Credits"}. The latest
version (and a more comprehensive AmigaGuide explanation of StrategoPrefs'
features) can always be found in aminet/game/board/@{B}StrategoPrefs.lha@{UB}
@{PAR}
@{CODE}
StrategoPrefs is an interface which simplifies the configuration of Stratego's
icon tooltypes via a @{B}MUI@{UB} interface. The various options are:

@{APEN 2}Stratego Setup - Sound@{APEN 1}

@{B}Sound:@{UB} Turns the sound on (checked) or off (unchecked). Default is on.
@{B}Fog of War:@{UB} Turns random background samples on (checked) or off (unchecked)
while playing the game. Default is on.

@{APEN 2}Stratego Setup - Initial Rules@{APEN 1}

@{B}Aggressor Advantage:@{UB} Turns @{"Rules - Aggressor Advantage" link AggressorAdvantage} on (checked) or off
(unchecked). Default is off.
@{B}Silent Defence:@{UB} Turns @{"Rules - Silent Defence" link SilentDefence} on (checked) or off (unchecked).
Default is off.
@{B}Rescue:@{UB} Turns @{"Rules - Rescue" link Rescue} on (checked) or off (unchecked). Default is off.

@{APEN 2}Stratego Setup - Display@{APEN 1}

@{B}Display:@{UB} This argument may be cycled between @{B}Workbench@{UB} (Stratego will open in a
window on Workbench) and @{B}Own Screen@{UB} (Stratego will open on its own
screen - this is the default).
@{B}Colours:@{UB} Stratego comes with two sets of graphics (@{B}ECS-16 colours@{UB} and
@{B}AGA/RTG-256 colours@{UB}). Use this cycle gadget to choose the desired option (see
@{"Requirements" link Require}. Deafult is @{B}ECS (16 Cols)@{UB}.

@{APEN 2}Stratego Setup - TCP Setup@{APEN 1}

@{B}TCP Enabled/Disabled:@{UB} Quite simply, turns Stratego TCP link on or off. Default
is off.
@{B}Server Name:@{UB} This field contains the DNS entry/IP address of the server which
Stratego will attempt to contact.
@{B}Port Number:@{UB} Defines the port Stratego will attempt to use. Default is 21000.

@{B}NOTE:@{UB} You may also use the @{B}Server List@{UB} (accessed via the Pop-up gadget on the
right side of the @{B}Server Name@{UB} field).

@{APEN 2}Stratego Setup - TCP Setup: Server List@{APEN 1}

@{B}Add:@{UB} Add a server to the server list. Brings up the @{B}Server Edit Window@{UB} to allow
you to edit the server entry.
@{B}Edit:@{UB} Brings up the @{B}Server Edit Window@{UB} and allows the currently selected server
to be edited.
@{B}Delete:@{UB} Deletes the selected server entry from the list.
@{B}Sort:@{UB} Sorts the servers on the TCP Entry/IP address.
@{B}Select:@{UB} Use the currently selected server.

@{APEN 2}Stratego Setup - TCP Setup: Server Edit Window@{APEN 1}

@{B}Alias:@{UB} Short name provided as a quick reference. If you type this in as the
server on the TCP Setup page it will be replaced by the full address.
@{B}Server Name:@{UB} Full DNS Entry/IP address of the server.
@{B}Port Number:@{UB} Port number to use.
@{B}Description:@{UB} Provided for you to type some text meaningful to yourself (such as
a comment). This field has no effect on the server settings.

