@{U}                                                                                @{UU}@{APEN 2}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{APEN 1}@{JLEFT}
@{B}AGGRESSOR/S@{UB} - switch initial state of @{"Rules - Aggressor Advantage" link AggressorAdvantage} on.
@{B}RESCUE/S@{UB} - switch initial state of @{"Rules - Rescue" link Rescue} on.
@{B}SILENT/S@{UB} - switch initial state of @{"Rules - Silent Defence" link SilentDefence} on.

@{B}R=RTG/S@{UB} - switch RTG (ie, 256 colours) mode on.
@{B}W=WORKBENCH/S@{UB} - run Stratego on WB.

@{APEN 2}WARNING:@{APEN 1} Due to datatypes remapping of the image files, this may take a while on
anything under an 030/040. The reason for the delay is the datatypes library
must remap all of the graphics to the WB palette. Before complaining, remember
how slow WB Patterns can be in the wrong situations.

@{B}NOTE:@{UB} Users of a RTG board should create a 640x400 x 8bit screenmode for
the optimal graphics resolution.

@{B}NOTE:@{UB} With @{B}Workbench@{UB} on, updates after dragging the window are somewhat slow.
This is Intuitions BitMap buffering, there is nothing we can do to significantly
improve the speed.  If you find it too slow, please run it on its own screen.

@{B}NOTE:@{UB} Unless you have an high-end Amiga with a graphics card, we do not
recommend RTG mode and WB mode both be switched on.

@{B}S=SOUNDOFF/S@{UB} - switch sound effects OFF.
@{B}F=FOGOFF/S@{UB} - switch "Fog of War" effects OFF. If @{B}SOUNDOFF@{UB} is specified, this
has no immediate effect.
@{U}                                                                                @{UU}@{APEN 2}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
